    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large pot with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bouillabaisse-style-cod-and-king-prawn-stew-with-buttery-ciabatta/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your<strong> potato[es]</strong> (skin on) into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> roughly</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bouillabaisse-style-cod-and-king-prawn-stew-with-buttery-ciabatta/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 450ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[600ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[750ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and stir it all together \u2013 this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bouillabaisse-style-cod-and-king-prawn-stew-with-buttery-ciabatta/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add<strong> half</strong> the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the pot with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>ground paprika</strong>, the <strong>chopped tomato </strong>and<strong> fennel seeds</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>chopped potato </strong>to the pot with your <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> and <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Stir it all together and bring to the boil over a high heat, then reduce the heat to medium and cook for 22-25 min or until the potatoes are tender</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bouillabaisse-style-cod-and-king-prawn-stew-with-buttery-ciabatta/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>remaining chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>ground paprika</strong> with the <strong>mayo </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>rouille</strong></p><p>On a separate board, chop your <strong>fish fillet[s]</strong> into large-bite sized pieces</p><p>Drain your <strong>king prawns</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bouillabaisse-style-cod-and-king-prawn-stew-with-buttery-ciabatta/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are tender, add the <strong>chopped fish </strong>to the pot with the <strong>drained king prawns</strong>, a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, then reduce to medium and cook for 4-5 min, stirring occasionally, or until the fish and prawns are cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>bouillabaisse-style fish & king prawn stew</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bouillabaisse-style-cod-and-king-prawn-stew-with-buttery-ciabatta/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>in half and place in the <strong>toaster</strong> for 1-2 min or until warmed through, then spread with a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Cut each buttered half into triangles \u2013 this is your<strong> buttery ciabatta</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bouillabaisse-style-cod-and-king-prawn-stew-with-buttery-ciabatta/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>bouillabaisse-style fish & king prawn stew</strong> in a bowl with the <strong>buttery ciabatta</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>rouille</strong> and season with a generous pinch of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
